<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF3FF9AFEB1FE6DFC0E5526" blockId="6.[191,1442,416,882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF3FF9AFEB1FE6DFE5E56BB" box="[256,403,452,478]" name="Colombia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF3FF9AFE2CFE6DFD6C56BA" box="[413,673,452,479]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Antioquia Department</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="4CFB9B23FFF3FF9AFD1DFE6DFD2B56BB" box="[684,742,452,478]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
N. Cañon del Río Claro Natural Reserve; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF3FF9AFB0EFE6DFA4B56BB" box="[1215,1414,452,478]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" value="2021-12-01">1 December 2021</date>
; J. Pruett. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFEE2FE4FFDB75564" authority="(Karsch)" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[339,634,486,513]" class="Arachnida" family="Dipluridae" genus="Linothele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericata">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF3FF9AFEE2FE4FFDDC5565" box="[339,529,486,512]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Linothele sericata</emphasis>
(Karsch)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFD36FE4FFCCB5564" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1889" box="[647,774,486,513]" class="Arachnida" family="Dipluridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dipluridae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp stood by the front right of the paralyzed curtain-web spider, examining it with her antennae, as it laid dorsal side upward on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF3FF9AFF79FD80FE835526" author="Pruett J." box="[200,334,553,579]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref26074" refString="Pruett J. 2021. Wasp has paralyzed tarantula. Available at https: // www. flickr. com / photos / 108136608 @ N 06 / 51760154507 / in / dateposted /. (Last accessed 31 December 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Pruett 2021</bibRefCitation>
; Pruett, Rochester, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF3FF9AFD94FD80FD525526" box="[549,671,553,579]" country="United States of America" name="Minnesota" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Minnesota</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF3FF9AFD1BFD80FD2F5526" box="[682,738,553,579]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">USA</collectingCountry>
, 2021 pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF3FF9AFEB1FDE2FDAF55AC" blockId="6.[191,1442,416,882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF3FF9AFEB1FDE2FE4A5500" box="[256,391,587,613]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">ECUADOR</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF3FF9AFE21FDE2FD715501" box="[400,700,586,613]" country="Ecuador" name="Morona-Santiago" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Morona Santiago Province</collectingRegion>
, Gualaquiza Canton, Chuchumblezo; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF3FF9AFBD4FDE2FACA5500" box="[1125,1287,587,613]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" value="2021-08-01">1 August 2021</date>
, 1544 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF3FF9AFAFFFDE2FAB45500" box="[1358,1401,587,613]" country="USA" name="Pratt Museum" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">PM</collectionCode>
; H. Casper (Caspersomeghost). Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFDF7FDC5FD0E55E2" box="[582,707,620,647]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Scytosiphonaceae" genus="Diplura" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytosiphonales" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF3FF9AFDF7FDC5FD5655E3" box="[582,667,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Diplura</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(undescribed) (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFCCBFDC5FC3455E2" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1889" box="[890,1017,620,647]" class="Arachnida" family="Dipluridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dipluridae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp examined the immobilized curtain-web spider with her antennae and mouthparts as it laid dorsal side upward on the ground surface (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF3FF9AFE74FD06FD9B55AC" author="Casper H." box="[453,598,687,713]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref21926" refString="Casper H. 2021. Spider Wasps (Family Pompilidae). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 90415681. (Last accessed 17 August 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Casper 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF3FF9AFEB1FD78FE965417" blockId="6.[191,1442,416,882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFF3FF9AFEB1FD78FC8F558E" box="[256,834,721,747]" collectorName="El Hatillo" country="Venezuela" location="Capital District" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Distrito Capital">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF3FF9AFEB1FD78FE69558E" box="[256,420,721,747]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">VENEZUELA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF3FF9AFE1EFD78FDAD558E" box="[431,608,721,747]" country="Venezuela" name="Distrito Capital" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Capital District</collectingRegion>
, Caracas, 
<collectorName id="26F65310FFF3FF9AFD62FD78FC8F558E" box="[723,834,721,747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">El Hatillo</collectorName>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF3FF9AFCFEFD78FC10558E" box="[847,989,721,747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" value="2021-07-26">26 July 2021</date>
; C. Rocha. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF3FF9AFB16FD78FE9B5468" authority="(Caporiacco)" baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1955" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Scytosiphonaceae" genus="Diplura" kingdom="Chromista" order="Scytosiphonales" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="petrunkevitchi">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF3FF9AFB16FD78FA6F558E" box="[1191,1442,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Diplura petrunkevitchi</emphasis>
(Caporiacco)
</taxonomicName>
, adult or subadult female. The wasp proceeded backwards on the ground, fanning its wings and grasping the immobilized curtain-web spider by its right pedipalp, at first, and, later, right forecoxa with her mandibles while maintaining it dorsal side upward (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF3FF9AFCA6FC9FFC6C5435" author="Rocha C." box="[791,929,822,848]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref26374" refString="Rocha C. 2021. Spider Wasp with Spider. Available at https: // www. instagram. com / p / CRy 5 _ bLn 1 iD /. (Last accessed 8 September 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Rocha 2021</bibRefCitation>
; Rocha, El Hatillo, Caracas, Venezuela, 2021 pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
